SIMPLE: salutary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Salutary
<hw>Sal"u*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>salutaris</ets>, from <ets>salus</ets>, <ets>-utis</ets>, health,
safety: cf. F. <ets>salutaire</ets>. See <er>Salubrious</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Wholesome; healthful; promoting health; <as>as,
<ex>salutary</ex> exercise</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Promotive of, or contributing to, some beneficial
purpose; beneficial; advantageous; <as>as, a <ex>salutary</ex>
design</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Wholesome; healthful; salubrious; beneficial;
useful; advantageous; profitable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sal"u*ta*ri*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
-- <wf>Sal"u*ta*ri*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salutation</ent>⟦br⟧
